<item>
            <title>[DATAMONGO-808] Spring data mongoDB not working with IPv6 address directly</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAMONGO-808</link>
                <project id="10701" key="DATAMONGO">Spring Data MongoDB</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I try use Ipv6 address for Spring data mongo. &lt;br/&gt;
In applicationContext.xml :&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;mongo:mongo host=&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;21::1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;  port=&quot;27017&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
or&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;mongo:mongo host=&quot;21::1&quot; port=&quot;27017&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Error:&lt;br/&gt;
Caused by: java.lang.NumberFormatException: For input string: &quot;:1]&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
I find file at com.mongodb.ServerAddress.&amp;lt;init&amp;gt;(ServerAddress.java:67).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-&amp;gt; I can&apos;t connect mongo server although I enabled IPv6 ( --ipv6=true )  in mongo server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Beside that, I used hostname in host file (etc/hosts)&lt;br/&gt;
Example: 21::1   mongo_address&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;mongo:mongo host=&quot;mongo_address&quot; port=&quot;27017&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-&amp;gt; Mongodb can work normal.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please help me to config mongodb with directly Ipv6 address!&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
